<item>
            <title>[QPIDJMS-557] ocassional connection failure log despite successfull requested connection closure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-557</link>
                <project id="12314524" key="QPIDJMS">Qpid JMS</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-528&quot; title=&quot;Improve logging of connection interruption and failure&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPIDJMS-528&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPIDJMS-528&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added some additional logging around connection interruption and failure. It has recently been seen to occasionally log connection failure even in cases where the connection was successfully closed as requested.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This looks to be from a race between notification of the remote side closing the socket and the client cleaning the provider/transport locally following a Close frame. This has likely always been the case and doesnt cause any other issue besides the spurious log message, so the simplest and least intrusive approach is just to ensure the new logging is gated when closure has been specifically requested.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
